{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff/orchestration (collectors -> aggregator -> summary input), not a single pure function. A unit test can miss wiring bugs (e.g., one source omitted) even if merge logic is correct. Higher levels were considered and rejected: behavior text only requires verifying payload composition, not real network/OS behavior or model output quality.","test_description":"Run the report assembly path with three source adapters wired in-process (stubbed responses for metrics, issue tracker, deployment log) and assert the exact payload sent to summary generation contains all three sections with source-identifying fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module fault handling: source client failure must propagate into report composition as a degraded section while the pipeline continues. Unit tests of fallback formatting alone can miss orchestration failures (early abort). Higher levels rejected: behavior does not require real network failure semantics, only correct handling of a source-failure signal.","test_description":"Wire fetchers + report builder in-process; configure one source adapter to raise an unavailable error while the other two return data; assert run completes, output includes a `data unavailable` marker only for the failed section, and no global abort occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the generated narrative content quality (faithfulness to input values). Mocked/stubbed generation would deterministically pass and hide real model misrepresentation/hallucination failures. Higher Workflow level rejected: this behavior evaluates one generation decision, not multiple agentic decisions chained.","test_description":"Execute summary generation against the real model using representative input fixtures with known key values; score outputs for factual alignment (required key numbers/entities present and not contradicted) across repeated runs with pass-rate thresholds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery path (network + email service/inbox). In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, transport, formatting, and acceptance issues that only appear end-to-end. Higher levels rejected: behavior asserts delivery completion, not model-quality correctness, and does not require multiple agentic decisions.","test_description":"Run the scheduled script end-to-end in a test environment with reachable source endpoints and a real test mailbox; verify message is delivered to configured recipient, with expected subject/body/attachments and no pipeline abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is